# Testing Standards

## Test Organization
- Write all tests inside `src/test` using Mocha and Chai
- Ensure tests are isolated, fast, and use real VSCode API mocks when needed
- No console logs or extra output in tests
- Use simple English (A2 level) and clear technical words only

## Test Requirements
- Tests should be fast and isolated
- Use real VSCode API mocks when needed
- No console output in tests
- Comprehensive coverage of formatting scenarios
- Test both positive and negative cases

## Test Structure
- Group tests by feature in subdirectories
- Use descriptive test names
- Keep test files focused on specific functionality
- Use fixtures for input/output comparison

## Key Test Files
- Test configuration: [src/test/testConfig.ts](mdc:src/test/testConfig.ts)
- Test utilities: [src/test/utils/fixtureLoader.ts](mdc:src/test/utils/fixtureLoader.ts)
- XML formatter tests: [src/test/xmlFormatterTest.ts](mdc:src/test/xmlFormatterTest.ts)
- Attribute tests: [src/test/attributes/](mdc:src/test/attributes/)
- Comment tests: [src/test/comments/](mdc:src/test/comments/)
- Formatting tests: [src/test/formatting/](mdc:src/test/formatting/)